Gemma Flanagan was left paralysed after being hit by Guillain Barre Syndrome , a rare condition which attacks the nervous system . 
  Aspiring model was working for British Airways when she felt heavy in her legs . 
  She assumed partying in heels was the cause of the pain - but she had the rare condition . 
  She spent seven months in a wheelchair and learned to talk and walk again . 
  Today she makes her catwalk debut in a show at London's Olympia . 
 